<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-11-25T14:38:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-11-25T14:38:00-05:00" n="343" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d343">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">320/11–2552: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">secret<lb/><gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss></hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">New
                                        York</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-11-25T14:38:00-05:00">November 25, 1952—2:38
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p><gloss target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 256. Dept pass New Delhi. Sent
                            New Delhi <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss> 5. Limited
                            distribution. From <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss>. Re Korea:</p>
                        <p>In further effort to meet Indian position, and in order to make absolute
                            minimum changes in Indian draft, US prepared to agree to accept first
                            sentence revised Indian version<note n="1" xml:id="d343fn1">The
                                reference was to the revised version of paragraph 17; for the text,
                                see telegram <gloss target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 246, Nov. 24,
                                    <ref target="#pg_676">p. 676</ref>.</note> as is, amending
                            second to read: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“If, at the end of a further thirty (30) days, there are any
                                    prisoners of war whose return to their homelands has not been
                                    effected under the above procedures, or whose future has not
                                    been provided for by the Political Conference, the
                                    responsibility for their care and disposition shall be
                                    transferred to a United Nations agency.”</p></quote></p>
                        <pb facs="0714" n="680" xml:id="pg_680"/>
                        <p>We hope this will lead to success in your efforts with <persName corresp="#p_NPJ1">Nehru</persName>, <gloss target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 252.<note n="2" xml:id="d343fn2"><hi rend="italic"><ref target="#d343">Supra</ref></hi>.</note></p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_ADG1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>